<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/75746507-arctander-alexander"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1585210977i/75746507._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/75746507-arctander-alexander">Arctander Alexander</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
It’s a play, but in many ways it reads like a novel because of Williams use of poetic prose in his scene and character descriptions.
</span>
</div>
