  <span id="freeText14801921387115765344" style="display:none">One of my favorite plays. I remember talking about it with a friend in high school, where we realized that from his perspective the play was about Tom, and from my perspective the play was about Laura. I guess it just depends who you are and where you are at in life.<br /><br />(I'm surprised I've never marked this as read before, and now I'll go off on a play spree.)<br /><br />"Being different is nothing to be ashamed of. Because other people are not such wonderful people. They're one hundred times one thousand. You're one times one! They walk all over the earth. You just stay here. They're common as — weeds, but — you — well, you're — Blue Roses!"</span>
